  "description": "Change of use from use class E(c)(ii) (Estate Agents) to use class Sui Generis (Hot food takeaway).",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "In the absence of information to demonstrate otherwise, the proposed takeaway use, by reason of noise and disturbance caused by customers entering and leaving the premises, vehicles parking and manoeuvring, particularly during the evening hours of operation, would be detrimental to the amenities of the occupiers of nearby residential properties, contrary to Havering Local Plan Policies 7 and 34, and London Plan (2021) policies D3, D14 and T7.",
    "In the absence of details for the provision of a fume extraction system or details to demonstrate how cooking odours and fumes would be emitted from the premises, the proposal by virtue of its proximity to residential flats, would have an unacceptable impact on the residential amenity due to increased levels of noise and vibration and odours associated with the kitchen facilities ancillary to the operation of a fast food takeaway contrary to Having Local Plan policies 13 and 34 and London Plan (2021) policy D14.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to the Agent by email on the 05/04/22."
  ],
